01:07:37.613 --> 01:07:54.353
Incoming livestream: So let's look at, some more examples of this. So here's a, a blocking of a destructive, command, a destructive action, so maybe we have some Cedar policies that, you know, look for SQL mutations that don't have any constraints, so in this case, like a delete from users without a where clause.

41
01:07:54.403 --> 01:08:05.203
Incoming livestream: So we can tell Claude to go run this. We can stop this and bring back, bring back the policy violation and context, for the agent then to use to either steer, or for a review by the user.

42
01:08:05.383 --> 01:08:22.212
Incoming livestream: We can also do, again, more sophisticated multi-turn things here with the stateful bookkeeping. We have, we can do information flow control, where maybe in this, in this case, we're using Gemini CLI. Maybe Gemini, we have, like, a name, a date of birth, and an address, right, some PII.

