01:10:55.213 --> 01:11:11.312
Incoming livestream: And then finally, just touching on, you know, more, the next, kind of future of, like, maybe multi-turn, stateful policies, you know, Cedar is inherently stateless, but because of the, entity and trajectory store, we can do bookkeeping about the entities that we observe and the trajectory over time.

58
01:11:11.313 --> 01:11:23.832
Incoming livestream: And allow us to expose those attributes as dynamic attributes, but there's other logic systems, like temporal, linear logic, and others that, have more support for those types of operations over time, over trajectories.

